          Job Description:
         BAE Systems is seeking qualified technical interns for our summer 2017 session. At BAE Systems, our interns spend their time collaborating with each other and our leadership to lead and create innovative, mission focused solutions to everyday challenges. All of this will lead to an engaging experience preparing you for the future. You will have the opportunity to apply your classroom experience in a challenging and fast paced business environment, and perform on meaningful work throughout the summer, while also supporting the development and growth of new skills in your chosen area of study.
         BAE Systems Intelligence & Security (I&S) enables the transformation of data into intelligence and provides engineering, integration and sustainment support for critical military platforms and systems for a diverse customer base ranging from the Department of Defense, to the intelligence community, federal and civilian agencies, and troops deployed around the world.
         LEAP Program Activities:
         At BAE Systems, we ensure every employee has access to training, career development programs and resources to make the most of their knowledge, interests and careers. We do this because our people are our core business.
         Our people take pride in supporting critical national security missions that protect our nation and those who serve. We
         invite you to participate in this critical mission via our 2017 Intelligence & Security LEAP Program. In this program you will build business acumen to solve real business challenges and have the opportunity to learn more about a range of intelligence programs and how they support national security. This will be achieved through engaging activities and building the right connections and relationships within the Intelligence and Security Sector.
         •Mentoring Partnerships
         •Developmental Modules (Leadership Panel, Resume Building, Interview Skills, Community Engagement)
         •Networking Events
         •Continuous Feedback and Meaningful work assignments
         •Process security clearance application (if applicable)
         Primary responsibilities:
         The primary responsibility for data science interns is to develop scripts and software to ingest and analyze information supporting data science related mission work.Successful candidates will be asked to contribute to a variety of pilot projects being conducted in a lab environment designed to allow staff to develop and enhance analytic tradecraft and tools. Selectees must be comfortable in a dynamic working environment with a small, multidisciplinary team and occasionally showing off work to visitors or meeting participants.
         Internship Period: Mid-May through Aug 2017
         All Intern positions are paid.
          Required Skills and Education:
         · Experience manipulating and combining data in various formats
         · Coursework in statistics
         · Coursework in programming (preferably Python)
          Preferred Skills and Education:
         · Sample projects (include Github or other link in resume)
         · Experience with GIS or map-based data visualization/UIs
         · Experience using APIs
          About BAE Systems Intelligence & Security:
         BAE Systems Intelligence & Security, based in McLean, Virginia, designs and delivers advanced defense, intelligence, and security solutions that support the important missions of our customers. Our pride and dedication shows in everything we do—from intelligence analysis, cyber operations and IT expertise to systems development, systems integration, and operations and maintenance services. Knowing that our work enables the U.S. military and government to recognize, manage and defeat threats inspires us to push ourselves and our technologies to new levels. That’s BAE Systems. That’s Inspired Work.
